<TITLE> Ittefaq journalists agree to work from Saturday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 3 (bdnews24.com)  The deadlock at the Ittefaq appears to be breaking as journalists and workers of the daily decided to go back to work Saturday, senior journalists said late Friday. The decision came from a meeting between the chairman of the editorial board Mainul Hosein, and a delegation of the journalists and employees, a senior journalist said. "We have reached an understanding with an owner. And so, journalists and workers will be rejoin duty Saturday," he said, preferring not to be named. "Whatever demands we have will be met in course of time in discussion with the owners." The crisis at one of the oldest and largest-selling broadsheets began Tuesday, forcing most journalists to skip work. The paper has been hitting the stands with reduced 16 pages. Mainul wrote a letter to district administration to appoint his wife Saju Hosein as a permanent publisher. But the district administration said Anwar Hossain Manju was still the publisher. bd
